<TITLE> UK envoy says he will welcome end to emergency </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 2 (bdnews24.com)  British High Commissioner Anwar Choudhury Tuesday said he would hail an end to emergency rule in Bangladesh. The British envoy spoke to reporters after a meeting with chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda in his Election Commission secretariat office. The EC is having talks with the political parties and the government said it would lift the ban on indoor politics as soon as possible, Choudhury said. He said Britain hoped the state of emergency and other prohibitions would be lifted as soon as possible. Choudhury said the government should make sure that people move freely and apply their voting rights properly and their safety ensured. British foreign and commonwealth office director for South Asia John Dennis and election commissioners Mohammad Sohul Hossain and M Sakhawat Hossain were present in the meeting. bdnew
